abstract: After a mix-up, and just before a winter storm, the former governor of New Mexico takes the red-eye from Arizona to meet the filing deadline in New Hampshire.
snippet: After a mix-up, and just before a winter storm, the former governor of New Mexico takes the red-eye from Arizona to meet the filing deadline in New Hampshire.
lead_paragraph: UPDATE 12:41 p.m: He made it! Gary Johnson filed for the New Hampshire Republican presidential primary, arriving at 11:15 a.m. to formally add his name to the state's ballot.

headline.main: Gary Johnson to Get His Name on the New Hampshire Ballot, Just in Time
